             (police-constable, G 154). I heard a cry of, Stop thief - I saw the prisoner run and turn the court; I knew it came round into Tabernacle-row - I ran round, and met him coming out of the court; I said, I wanted him - I took him back and met the prosecutor with the handkerchief in his hand.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. We met the prosecutor with the handkerchief, but he is decidedly wrong in saying it was me.</p>
